{#
    With this template, you can adjust the modal open behavior to open on page visit.

    It is recommended to create a variant of this template to adjust it to your needs.

    Following possiblities:

    - Change layout to bootstrap 5 (or any other layout, if a template is provided):
        Replace the extends statement with:
        {% extends "@Contao/content_element/pwa_push_subscription_popup/bs5_modal.html.twig" %}

    - Adjust the open behavior:

        Active the open on page visit behavior by setting the variable `open_on_init` to `true` (already set in this template).
        {% set open_on_init = true %}

        Delay the open behavior by setting the variable `open_delay` to the desired delay in milliseconds (default: 0).
        {% set open_delay = 500 %}

        Show the popup again after a certain time (in hours) by setting the variable `expire_time` (default: 0 / off).
        {% set expire_time = 168 %}

    Hint: if you want the open on init behavior, don't forget to remove the open button like shown in this template (by overriding the `button_open` block).

#}

{% extends "@Contao/content_element/pwa_push_subscription_popup.html.twig" %}
{#{% extends "@Contao/content_element/pwa_push_subscription_popup/bs5_modal.html.twig" %}#}

{% block button_open %}
{% endblock %}

{% block script %}
    {% set open_on_init = true %}
{#    {% set open_delay = 500 %}#}
{#    {% set expire_time = 168 %}#}
    {{ parent() }}
{% endblock %}